# Database Models

The application uses MongoDB with Mongoose for data modeling. Here are the main models:

## Admin Model
- [src/models/Admin.js](mdc:src/models/Admin.js) - Admin user model for dashboard access

## User Model
- [src/models/User.js](mdc:src/models/User.js) - End user model

## Pet Model
- [src/models/Pet.js](mdc:src/models/Pet.js) - Pet information model with owner relationship

## Theme Model
- [src/models/Theme.js](mdc:src/models/Theme.js) - Theme customization options

## UserTheme Model
- [src/models/UserTheme.js](mdc:src/models/UserTheme.js) - Association between users and their selected themes

## Database Connection
The MongoDB connection is established in [src/server.js](mdc:src/server.js) using the MONGODB_URI environment variable.
